arch:property.oc:show_val: Soil below the blockage within the northern west niche of the ‘bathroom’

Phase X: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.

Locus 62 is the soil below the blockage within the northern west semicircular niche (part of Locus 60) of the bathroom. The soil is a fine loose sand (Munsell 7.5 YR 5/4 brown), with inclusions of plaster, pottery and bone. The soil is likely the result of dumping for the filling in of the niche just before its blockage. Locus 62 is therefore phased to Stage 5.
Full blockage, robbing out and dumping.
0.63 m north south -by- 0.48 m east west.
